s improved.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1474:"<p>New GD bbPress Toolbox Pro 1.6 two new modules: control over fancy editor for topics and for fancy editor for replies. Both include several options that are disabled by default from bbPress 2.3. Option is added to disable any number of BBCodes. Custom views query handling is improved.</p>\n<p>bbPress 2.3 has changed the way it handles editor. If you enable fancy editor in bbPress options, you will not get full tinyMCE editor as before. To do this, you can now use modules in this plugin to handle topic and reply editors separately. Options include: TinyMCE editor, Media buttons, compact toolbar, WPAutoP filter and size of the editor.</p>\n<p>WordPress 3.6 will add some shortcodes that will interfere with the BBCodes (YouTube and Vimeo). So, you can now disable any number of BBCodes this plugin adds to avoid potential conflicts with WordPress or other plugins. Custom views code is improved and updated for better handling of the queries used to get views topics.</p>\n<p>As always, please report in forums any issues you maybe find with this latest version.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-green"><h3>Official Website</h3>\n<p>GD bbPress Toolbox Pro has own website:</p>\n<p>Home: <a href="http://www.gdbbpbox.com/" target="_blank">www.gdbbpbox.com</a></div>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-bbpress-toolbox-pro-1-6/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellfo