i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2125:"<p>New version GD Products Center Pro 1.2.1 brings another set of bug fixes (related to installation, update, filters, compare page and compare box), several small new features and updates (control visibility of compare box, improvements to admin side menu icons display).</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-red" style="font-size: 1.1em;"><strong>Important:</strong> In April new 1.2.2 will be released that will drop support for WordPress 3.2 and will requires WordPress 3.3 to work. Such transition is caused by April/May release of WordPress 3.6 (read <strong><a title="Updates for WordPress 3.6" href="http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/announcements/updates-for-wordpress-3-6/">this</a></strong> for more information).</div>\n<p>Several problems caused by the company type updates are now resolved. These problems happened during update or install of the plugin when in some cases, parts of the plugin update was not executed. All these should be resolved with this version. Many problems with filters are resolved, most important one was issue with the company types filters. Compare box and compare page also received several important fixes.</p>\n<p>Some other bugs reported were caused by the update problems. So, update to 1.2.1, and try again. If the same bugs are still appearing, please let me know. As always, please report all problems in the forums. Please be as specific as possible, and include error log reports or JavaScript errors that might have been reported in browser.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-blue"><strong>More Information:</strong><br />\n<a href="http://www.dev4press.com/plugins/gd-products-center/" target="_blank">www.dev4press.com/plugins/gd-products-center</a></p>\n<p><strong>Support Forum:</strong><br />\n<a href="http://www.dev4press.com/forums/forum/plugins/gd-products-center/" target="_blank">www.dev4press.com/forums/forum/plugins/gd-products-center</a></div>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-1-pro-1/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-1-pro-1/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:24;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:72:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"Updates for WordPress 3.6";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/announcements/updates-for-wordpress-3-6/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/announcements/updates-for-wordpress-3-6/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 25 Mar 2013 13:05:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:11:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"big problem";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"core functions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"event binding";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"important updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"javascript code";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"jquery";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"jQueryUI";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"target release date";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://www.dev4press.com/?p=20205";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:283:"WordPress 3.6 is in development with target release date set to April 29 2013. This version includes new jQuery 1.9 that includes several important updates that will break all JavaScript code in all of our plugins or themes. And this is big problem for older WordPress compatibility.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3117:"<p>WordPress 3.6 is in development with target release date set to April 29 2013. This version includes new jQuery 1.9 that includes several important updates that will break all JavaScript code in all of our plugins or themes. And this is big problem for older WordPress compatibility.</p>\n<p>jQuery 1.9.1 (currently in WordPress 3.6 development builds) removes some core functions that many plugins rely on, and that includes live() method for event binding, and all other bind related functions. In jQuery 1.7.1 a new method is added: on(). So, we need to have all plugins jQuery code updated to use on() instead of live() and bind(). jQuery 1.7.1 is shipped with WordPress 3.3. And because of that, all plugins will get updated jQuery code that will require jQuery 1.7.1 and with that will require WordPress 3.3.</p>\n<p>Currently, there was a plan to change requirements for some plugins to WP 3.3, and that plan will go ahead earlier than planned (GD Products Center and GD bbPress Toolbox). And some plugins already require WP 3.3 (GD Custom Posts And Taxonomies Tools 4.1 Pro that will be released this week). But, now all that is changed, and there will many updates during April to stay ahead of WP 3.6 launch. It is very possible that WP 3.6 is not going to be released until late May, depending on how many delays there will be.</p>\n<p>During March there are 3 releases planned:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>GD Products Center 1.2.1 (March 26), it will still work WordPress 3.2.</li>\n<li>GD Custom Posts and Taxonomies Tools 4.1 (March 27), it will require WordPress 3.3.</li>\n<li>GD bbPress Toolbox 1.5 (March 31), it will require WordPress 3.3.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In April more updates are coming, all will require WordPress 3.3:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>xScape Theme Framework 1.9.2 (middle of April).</li>\n<li>GD Products Center 1.2.2 (in late April).</li>\n<li>GD aZon Fusion 0.9.7 (in early April).</li>\n<li>GD Affiliate Center 1.4 (in late April).</li>\n<li>GD Simple Widgets 2.2.1 (middle of April).</li>\n<li>GD Press Tools 4.4.2 (in late April or early May).</li>\n<li>All 3 bbPress free plugins (first week of April).</li>\n<li>Other free plugins that rely on jQuery (in late April).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Some of these plugins all rely on jQueryUI, and they will also get latest available jQueryUI.</p>\n<p>And in the future, plan is to limit support for maximum of 4 versions of WordPress. Once WordPress 3.7 gets in development, minimum required WordPress for plugins and themes will shift to WP 3.4, or WP 3.5 (for some plugins, depending on what they need or do).</p>\n<p>My suggestion is to make sure that other plugins you use are also ready for the WordPress 3.6 transition, since now you need to worry about jQuery too, and I think that a lot of plugins will not be ready for such upgrade. Try to reach to developers of plugins you use and remind them of the upcoming changes to WordPress so they will have enough time to prepare for it.</p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/announcements/updates-for-wordpress-3-6/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/announcements/updates-for-wordpress-3-6/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:25;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:72:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"GD Products Center 1.2.0.2 Pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-2-pro/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-2-pro/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 16 Mar 2013 17:55:12 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:11:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"cache";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"cache methods";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Cleanup group";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"company types";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"conditional checks";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"Object cache methods";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"plugin functions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"problematic cache methods";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Total Cache plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"unmodified version";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://www.dev4press.com/?p=20144";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:271:"Maintenance release for GD Products Center Pro is here with few more bug fixes and changes. These are small updates for some of the plugin functions related to conditional checks and compare box. Some warnings are also fixed related to some plugins conditional functions.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3104:"<p>Maintenance release for GD Products Center Pro is here with few more bug fixes and changes. These are small updates for some of the plugin functions related to conditional checks and compare box. Some warnings are also fixed related to some plugins conditional functions.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-red" style="font-size: 1.1em;"><strong>Important:</strong> New version introduces some very important changes. Please take the time to read this post in detail, and also to watch upgrade guide for migration to this new version: <a title="Upgrade Guide: Migration to Brand in v1.2" href="http://www.dev4press.com/2013/tutorials/plugins/gd-products-center/upgrade-guide-migration-to-brand-in-v1-2/">Upgrade Guide: Migration to Brand in v1.2</a></div>\n<p>Couple of users reported that after upgrade to 1.2/1.2.0.1 Brand and Seller company types were not created. No matter what I tried and on how many setups, I couldn&#8217;t reproduce the problem. All test I did with normal and unmodified WordPress installation and unmodified version of the plugin, every time update was OK and company types were added.</p>\n<p>The one instance that this failed was installation that was using W3 Total Cache plugin with Database and Object cache active. When one of these is active, plugin update is not saved to database correctly, and update fails. I presume that any other plugin with these types of cache will produce same problems. I have said many times before: these two types of cache can cause many problems since they will server old data, and will not save data always as expected. If you insist on using this type of cache, I can&#8217;t help you, and I can&#8217;t solve problems caused by Database or Object cache methods!</p>\n<p>If you have update problems, and you don&#8217;t use these problematic cache methods, please report in the forums if you have some errors in the server error log related to this plugin after update. Also, any other errors in the log can point to a problem with some other plugin that can cause issues here. All plugin updates are performed when <strong>after_theme_setup</strong> action is executed by WordPress. I will try to resolve the issues, if they are related to my plugin. Just make sure to leave detailed report about all this.</p>\n<p>There is a way to manually attempt creation of company types from Tools panel: Open Maintenance tab, Cleanup group, check Recreate Default Companies and click Execute for Cleanup group.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-blue"><strong>More Information:</strong><br />\n<a href="http://www.dev4press.com/plugins/gd-products-center/" target="_blank">www.dev4press.com/plugins/gd-products-center</a></p>\n<p><strong>Support Forum:</strong><br />\n<a href="http://www.dev4press.com/forums/forum/plugins/gd-products-center/" target="_blank">www.dev4press.com/forums/forum/plugins/gd-products-center</a></div>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-2-pro/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-2-pro/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:26;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:69:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"GD Products Center 1.2.0.1 Pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-1-pro/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-1-pro/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Mar 2013 15:04:13 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:10:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"brand information";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"bug fixes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"bugs";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"company types";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"New update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"permalinks rules";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"redirection";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"registration data";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"upgrade";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://www.dev4press.com/?p=20093";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:264:"Maintenance release for GD Products Center Pro is here with few more bug fixes that have crawled into stable 1.2 release yesterday. This fixes import/export issues, compare box limit issue, creating theme templates problems and problems with editing company types.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2856:"<p>Maintenance release for GD Products Center Pro is here with few more bug fixes that have crawled into stable 1.2 release yesterday. This fixes import/export issues, compare box limit issue, creating theme templates problems and problems with editing company types.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-red" style="font-size: 1.1em;"><strong>Important:</strong> New version introduces some very important changes. Please take the time to read this post in detail, and also to watch upgrade guide for migration to this new version: <a title="Upgrade Guide: Migration to Brand in v1.2" href="http://www.dev4press.com/2013/tutorials/plugins/gd-products-center/upgrade-guide-migration-to-brand-in-v1-2/">Upgrade Guide: Migration to Brand in v1.2</a></div>\n<p>New update is added to fix the issues reported since the release of the 1.2 yesterday (10 bugs are fixed), and to add importing of brand information that was missing from 1.2. Tool for manual reset of company types is also added.</p>\n<p>Few more things about upgrade:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>If you have any issues with links, redirection or broken pages, clear the permalinks rules, or try to cleanup registration data from plugins Tools panel, Maintenance -&gt; Cleanup. Also, if you delete taxonomy from plugin, do the same thing, and also visit Permalinks panel under WordPress Settings.</li>\n<li>If you don&#8217;t see Brands and Sellers menus in the WordPress admin, than something was wrong with upgrade. You can manually trigger creation of company types from Tools panel, Maintenance -&gt; Cleanup -&gt; Recreate Default Companies. If this also doesn&#8217;t help, check if the plugin is installed OK, with all files available.</li>\n<li>Theme templates are not changed, and there is no need to create them again for any of the product types. 1.2 did changed some of <strong>rendering</strong> templates.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Known Issues:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Export of prices for sellers is not included yet. It will be separate export feature and it will be added soon.</li>\n<li>Export/Import of companies settings is not included yet, and it will be added in one of the future versions.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>As always, please test new version and report all problems in the support forum.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-blue"><strong>More Information:</strong><br />\n<a href="http://www.dev4press.com/plugins/gd-products-center/" target="_blank">www.dev4press.com/plugins/gd-products-center</a></p>\n<p><strong>Support Forum:</strong><br />\n<a href="http://www.dev4press.com/forums/forum/plugins/gd-products-center/" target="_blank">www.dev4press.com/forums/forum/plugins/gd-products-center</a></div>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-1-pro/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/plugins-news/gd-products-center-1-2-0-1-pro/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"