xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://www.dev4press.com/?p=20003";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:259:"Development process for new GD Products Center 1.2 is in full power, and this new version will include some very important core changes that aim to improve user experience with products comparison and products classification with different company post types.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1750:"<p>Development for new GD Custom Posts And Taxonomies Tools 4.1 is ongoing,with some changes in the plugin plans, new version will be released sooner than previously planned. 4.1 will have smaller change-set, with focus on stability, code cleanup and some new features.</p>\n<p>Plugin will get new settings for post types and taxonomies added in recent WordPress 3.5, and it will no longer support WordPress 3.2. Due to increasing number of problems due to changes in different WP versions in the past two years, maintaining support for more than 3 WP version is becoming very difficult. Considering that most of other WP developers only support latest WP version, Dev4Press plugin will still support as many versions as possible as long as that doesn&#8217;t affect plugin expansion, code stability and problems that can be caused by old versions code. Dropping WP 3.2 support will cleanup JavaScript (no more support for old jQuery 1.3/1.4, and old jQueryUI 1.8), cleanup and code removal for some critical core elements (templates, rewrite rules) and few other things.</p>\n<p><span class="Apple-style-span" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.292969); -webkit-composition-fill-color: rgba(175, 192, 227, 0.230469); -webkit-composition-frame-color: rgba(77, 128, 180, 0.230469);">If you have some suggestions about minor changes that could be added to this version or bugs to report, please do so in the forum. It is expected to release new GD Custom Posts And Taxonomies Tools 4.1 by the end of March 2013.</span></p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/development/gd-custom-posts-and-taxonomies-tools-4-1-pro/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:97:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/development/gd-custom-posts-and-taxonomies-tools-4-1-pro/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:30;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:69:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"SMART Plugins: Smart Posts Index";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/smart-plugins/smart-posts-index/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://w