ive HTML5 theme skyScape coming soon.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1585:"<p>New version of xScape Theme Framework and xScape Core theme, brings more important features and imporvements that were a bit late to go into 1.9 version last week. All the changes in this version are needed for our first fully responsive HTML5 theme skyScape coming soon.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-red"><strong>Upgrade Information:</strong> New framework requires WordPress 3.2 or newer to work. Themes using the framework must be updated after you switch to new xScape Core 1.9.1. Make sure you backup your theme before proceeding, just in case.</div>\n<p>xScape now contains<a href="http://d4p.me/ccsrb" target="_blank"> Smart Responsive Breadcrumbs</a> jQuery and CSS plugin, but only new themes will be able to use it, making changes to old themes would be too complicated to do. Breadcrumbs rendering is rewritten to allow for more flexibility. Grid layouts are improved, and responsive grid is fully functional. Shortcodes are improved, and some of them can now use Font Awesome icons. Networks widget is improved to use icons from Zocial font instead of images. There are other core changes that will further improve framework stability.</p>\n<p>Themes lightScape and Serenity are also updated with few more changes and fixes missing from previous releases. If you notice any issues with the framework or themes, please let me know through support forums.</p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/themes-news/xscape-framework-and-core-1-9-1/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/themes-news/xscape-framework-and-core-1-9-1/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:36;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:72:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"SMART Plugins: Smart Responsive Breadcrumbs";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:78:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/smart-plugins/smart-responsive-breadcrumbs/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/smart-plugins/smart-responsive-breadcrumbs/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 22 Feb 2013 10:25:13 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:11:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"SMART Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"breadcrumbs";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"CodeCanyon";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base